      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok i get the socioeconomic stuff but even if it isn't a simple direct cause, the argument for banning certain types of weapons or making background checks harder is based on actual science and public health data. it feels like the people arguing against it are just using constitutional technicalities to ignore the actual evidence that these laws save lives. dont you think the scientific evidence should carry more weight than just legal interpretations?",
